{"word":"ὁμῆλιξ","slug":"ὁμῆλιξ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὁμῆλιξ</b></el> <el>(ὁμ-ῆλιξ, ῐκος,) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>of the same age</i>, mostly of young persons, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a> <i>an equal in age, comrade</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>aequalis</el>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>of like stature</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}